      "cefrLevel": "C2",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "Plural of animalculum: very small, usually microscopic organisms that are almost impossible to see with the naked eye, now an old-fashioned scientific term.",
          "examples": [
            "Under the early microscopes, scientists believed they saw countless animalculae swimming in a drop of pond water.",
            "He wrote about the animalculae in blood, long before modern microbiology developed."
